</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[707,1194,441,1339]" pageId="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,1265,1286]" pageId="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
The trivial name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[1034,1115,1264,1285]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="helvinus">
<emphasis box="[1034,1115,1264,1285]" italics="true" pageId="7">helvinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= yellowish) is a Latin adjective that refers to the yellow coloration of the legs.
</paragraph>
